                    <i class="fas fa-envelope"></i>
                </div>
                <h4>Email Integration</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li>Email confirmation system</li>
                    <li>Password reset emails</li>
                    <li>Email change notifications</li>
                    <li>Account security alerts</li>
                    <li>Configurable email templates</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="no-code-section">
        <h2>You Don't Need to Write Authentication Code</h2>
        <p>The most important thing to understand is that <strong>all the complex authentication code is already written for you</strong>. Here's what you <strong>don't</strong> need to do:</p>
        
        <div class="dont-do-grid">
            <div class="dont-do-item">
                <div class="dont-icon">
                    <i class="fas fa-times-circle"></i>
                </div>
                <h5>Don't Write Login Logic</h5>
                <p>No need to write code that checks usernames and passwords. .NET Identity handles this securely.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="dont-do-item">
                <div class="dont-icon">
                    <i class="fas fa-times-circle"></i>
                </div>
                <h5>Don't Hash Passwords</h5>
                <p>No need to learn cryptographic algorithms. Passwords are automatically hashed using industry-standard methods.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="dont-do-item">
                <div class="dont-icon">
                    <i class="fas fa-times-circle"></i>
                </div>
                <h5>Don't Manage Sessions</h5>
                <p>No need to create session tokens or manage cookie expiration. Session management is built-in.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="dont-do-item">
                <div class="dont-icon">
                    <i class="fas fa-times-circle"></i>
                </div>
                <h5>Don't Build Security Features</h5>
                <p>No need to implement account lockout, brute force protection, or other security measures. They're included.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        
